Class QualityHashMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.cantido.qlearner.algorithm.quality.QualityHashMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    QualityMap

    @NotThreadSafe
public class QualityHashMap
extends Object
implements QualityMap
    A data structure that stores Quality values in a hashed form.

      • QualityHashMap

        public QualityHashMap(@Nonnegative
                      int expectedStates,
                      @Nonnegative
                      int actionsPerState)
        Constructs an empty QualityHashMap with a specified number of expected total states and number of expected actions per state.

        Specifying these values is only a performance optimization. It does not change the functionality of this object.

        Parameters:
        expectedStates - the approximate total count of states this object will store.
        actionsPerState - the average count of actions that each stored state will have.
